# Pre-Commit CI Checks

**CRITICAL**: Before every `git commit`, run the EXACT commands CI uses. Do NOT lint only changed files -- CI lints everything.

## Required checks (run both, in order):

```powershell
ruff check src/ tests/
python -m pytest tests/ -x -q --tb=short
```

## Why this matters

CI runs `ruff check src/ tests/` across ALL files. Running ruff on only the files you edited misses:
- Unused imports in new test files
- Import sorting violations
- Line length violations in files you created but didn't re-check

This has caused CI failures 3+ times. Always lint the full scope.

## Checklist before committing

1. `ruff check src/ tests/` -- zero errors (use `--fix` first, then manual fixes for E501)
2. `pytest tests/ -x -q` -- all tests pass
3. Only then: `git add . ; git commit ...`
